16/12/2008
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The speaker of the Belgrade city assembly, Branislav Belic, resigned on Monday (December 15th) citing personal reasons. 
Belic said the ruling coalition in Belgrade will nominate Serbian Socialist Party member Aleksandar Antic as his successor. 
Belgrade Mayor Dragan Gilas said Antik's position in the city assembly will be filled by Democratic Party member Zoran Alimpic. 
(B92, Beta, MIA - 15/12/08)
